TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(5, 25, 1);
$b = random($a+2, 50, 1);
$c = random(int(1.3*$a), 50, 1);

$n = random(3,8,1);

$ans1 = $a/$b;

$ans2 = "1 - $a/x";

$ans3 = 1 - (1 - $a/$c)**$n;

BEGIN_TEXT

You'll need to use the formatted text mode in order to do this problem: click the "formatted text" button on the bottom of
the page and then click "submit answers". $PAR

The probability density function of \(X\), the lifetime of a certain type of device (measured in months), is given by 

\[f(x)= \left\{ "\{" \} \begin{array}{ll}
0              & \mbox{if \ } x<$a \cr
\frac{$a}{x^2} & \mbox{if \ } x>$a 
\end{array} \right. \]

Find the following: $BR

\( P(X>$b) = \)\{ans_rule(10)\} $BR

The cumulative distribution function of \(X\):   

\[F(x)= \left\{ "\{" \} \begin{array}{ll}
\{tex_ans_rule(10)\} & \mbox{if \ } x<$a \cr
\{tex_ans_rule(10)\} & \mbox{if \ } x>$a 
\end{array} \right. \] 

The probability that at least one out of \($n\) devices of this type will function for at least \($c\) months:
\{ans_rule(10)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(fun_cmp(0));
ANS(fun_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

